# Coding Standards

## Scaffolding Only

When creating new features, components, or modules:

- **Only scaffold** — create the files, folders, and basic structure (exports, types, empty function signatures)
- **Do NOT implement** the internal logic unless explicitly asked to
- This applies to components, utilities, hooks, API routes, server actions, and any new code

```tsx
// ✅ Scaffold — create the file with the shell, export, and props type
export default function RecommenderModal({ open, onClose }: RecommenderModalProps) {
  // TODO: implement
  return null;
}

// ❌ Don't — fill in full implementation without being asked
export default function RecommenderModal({ open, onClose }: RecommenderModalProps) {
  const [step, setStep] = useState<'quiz' | 'loading' | 'results'>('quiz');
  const [answers, setAnswers] = useState({});
  // ... full implementation ...
}
```
